        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Insulated Vehicle&quot; scheme was launched by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India, under the umbrella scheme &quot;Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana&quot;. It aims to promote efficient and hygienic fish transportation systems. Under this scheme, a financial grant is provided to the beneficiaries for purchasing insulated (reefer) vehicles used in fish transportation. It seeks to minimize post-harvest losses, improve fish value chains, and enhance earnings of fish farmers by enabling cold-chain logistics.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Financial Assistance:**\n\n- Financial grant of up to ₹20,00,000/- per unit for the purchase of an insulated (reefer) vehicle.\n\n**Grant Limits:**\n\n- 40% of the unit cost for general category beneficiaries.\n- 60% of the unit cost for Scheduled Caste (SC) and women beneficiaries.\n\n> **Note**\n\n\n- Subsidy is applicable for one vehicle per beneficiary only.\n- Central assistance is released only after initiating fishery activity.\n- The applicant should agree that any losses in procurement, operation, or maintenance are their own responsibility, and not that of the Government of India or Haryana.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide a subsidy per unit for purchasing insulated vehicles for the beneficiaries to promote cold-chain logistics in fish transportation.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The \"Insulated Vehicle\" scheme was launched by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry & Dairying, Government of India, under the umbrella scheme \"Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana\". It aims to promote efficient and hygienic fish transportation systems. Under this scheme, a financial grant is provided to the beneficiaries for purchasing insulated (reefer) vehicles used in fish transportation. It seeks to minimize post-harvest losses, improve fish value chains, and enhance earnings of fish farmers by enabling cold-chain logistics."
              }
